  "local_port": 44756,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which companies in Silicon Valley hire/are likely to hire computational biologists?",
  "response": "Silicon Valley is home to numerous companies that are actively involved in biotechnology, bioinformatics, and computational biology. Here are some key companies that are known to hire or are likely to hire computational biologists:\n\n1. **Google (Verily Life Sciences)**\n   - Google's healthcare arm, Verily, works on various projects that involve computational biology, such as precision medicine and genomic data analysis.\n\n2. **Illumina**\n   - A leading company in DNA sequencing and array-based technologies, Illumina often seeks computational biologists to work on data analysis and algorithm development.\n\n3. **23andMe**\n   - Known for personal genomics and biotechnology, 23andMe employs computational biologists to analyze genetic data and develop new research insights.\n\n4. **Grail**\n   - Grail focuses on early cancer detection through blood tests and relies heavily on computational biology for data analysis and algorithm development.\n\n5. **Genentech**\n   - A major biotech company, Genentech often hires computational biologists for drug discovery and development projects.\n\n6. **Invitae**\n   - Invitae specializes in genetic testing and employs computational biologists to interpret genetic data and develop new tests.\n\n7. **Pacific Biosciences (PacBio)**\n   - A company specializing in long-read sequencing technologies, PacBio needs computational biologists to develop and improve their sequencing algorithms.\n\n8. **Element Biosciences**\n   - A newer player in the sequencing market, Element Biosciences often seeks computational biologists for their technology development efforts.\n\n9. **Recursion Pharmaceuticals**\n   - Though primarily based in Salt Lake City, Recursion has a presence in Silicon Valley and hires computational biologists for their drug discovery platform.\n\n10. **NVIDIA**\n    - While primarily known for graphics processing units, NVIDIA is increasingly involved in healthcare and hires computational biologists for their AI and drug discovery initiatives.\n\n11. **Thermo Fisher Scientific**\n    - With a presence in Silicon Valley, Thermo Fisher Scientific hires computational biologists for their life sciences and diagnostics divisions.\n\n12. **Guardant Health**\n    - Focused on liquid biopsy and cancer diagnostics, Guardant Health often looks for computational biologists to work on their data analysis pipelines.\n\nThese companies typically post job openings on their websites, as well as on job boards like LinkedIn, Indeed, and specialized biotech job portals. Keeping an eye on these platforms and networking within the computational biology community can help in finding opportunities in Silicon Valley.",
